<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[839,1467,1013,1302]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,946,1013,1037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Small (length 
<quantity box="[1102,1191,1013,1038]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
), yellowish brown species, similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1855" box="[953,1051,1044,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1051,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Ptecticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by the: frons wide and almost parallel in females; face slightly anteroventrally produced to form a small beak-like protuberance that is visible in profile; scutum with a distinct black medial stripe; wings with vein 
<emphasis box="[1030,1061,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1053,1061,1173,1187]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1121,1151,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1143,1151,1173,1187]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
extremely weak and nearly unpigmented between cells 
<emphasis box="[1152,1176,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">br</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1236,1269,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">bm</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[1287,1317,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1309,1317,1202,1216]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1377,1408,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1400,1408,1202,1216]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
very weakly developed; 
<emphasis box="[1053,1083,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1075,1083,1232,1246]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">4</subScript>
</emphasis>
issued from discal cell (i.e. 
<emphasis box="[1403,1466,1219,1246]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
dM 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1439,1466,1232,1246]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3+4</subScript>
</emphasis>
absent); alula reduced, almost linear; and lower calypter linear, without projecting process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[839,1467,1323,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,941,1323,1347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Remarks</emphasis>
. Regarding the New Guinean fauna, 
<taxonomicName authority="de Meijere, 1913" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Chrysochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Chrysochlora lineata</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation author="Meijere, J. C. H. de" box="[952,1104,1352,1376]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="305 - 386" refId="ref11913" refString="Meijere, J. C. H. de. 1913. Dipteren I. Resultats de l'Expedition Scientifique Neerlandaise a la Nouvelle-Guinee. Nova Guinea 9: 305 - 386." type="journal article" year="1913">Meijere, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="James" authorityYear="1939" box="[1317,1460,1353,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Formosargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1460,1353,1376]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Formosargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing the characters noted above in the diagnosis. Therefore, we propose moving the species into the latter genus, to become 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Meijere, 1913)" authorityName="Lessard &amp; Yeates &amp; Woodley" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1034,1467,1440,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Formosargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[1034,1258,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Formosargus lineata</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Meijere, J. C. H. de" box="[1307,1459,1440,1464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="305 - 386" refId="ref11913" refString="Meijere, J. C. H. de. 1913. Dipteren I. Resultats de l'Expedition Scientifique Neerlandaise a la Nouvelle-Guinee. Nova Guinea 9: 305 - 386." type="journal article" year="1913">Meijere, 1913</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,1034,1469,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[839,1034,1469,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
